Class Implementor

java.lang.Object
info.kgeorgiy.ja.chulkov.implementor.Implementor
All Implemented Interfaces:
Impler, JarImpler
public class Implementor extends Object implements JarImpler
Implementation of JarImpler, that generates implementations of interfaces and classes with default behavior.

      private String getClassPath(Class<?> token)

      Parameters:
      token - Class for finding classpath of it
      Returns:
      classpath or empty string if classpath is unavailable

    • implement

      public void implement(Class<?> token, Path root) throws ImplerException
      Description copied from interface: Impler
      Produces code implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

      Generated class' name should be the same as the class name of the type token with Impl suffix added. Generated source code should be placed in the correct subdirectory of the specified root directory and have correct file name. For example, the implementation of the interface List should go to $root/java/util/ListImpl.java

      Specified by:
      implement in interface Impler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      root - root directory.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated.

    • implementAndReturnFilePath

      private Path implementAndReturnFilePath(Class<?> token, Path root) throws ImplerException
      Same as implement(java.lang.Class<?>, java.nio.file.Path), but returns path to implemented java file.
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      root - root directory
      Returns:
      path to implemented java file
      Throws:
      ImplerException - if token can't be implemented

    • generatePackage

      private String generatePackage(Class<?> token)
      Generate package line about token. If package isn't present, returns empty string. If token has package my.best.package, returns package line with two line separators after 
           package my.best.package;
      Parameters:
      token - type to getting package
      Returns:
      package lines string if package is present, or empty string otherwise
